                            <comment id="475664" author="gerrit" created="Tue, 21 Oct 2025 18:10:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;Maximilian Dilger &amp;lt;mdilger@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&quot; uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/61943&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/61943&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19054&quot; title=&quot;allow limiting the number of clients connected to the filesystem&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19054&quot;&gt;LU-19054&lt;/a&gt; utils: New max client connect limit.&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: 1&lt;br/&gt;
Commit: d6e9c98688f4187fc0943208a31f9c4d62c72807&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="475238" author="adilger" created="Thu, 16 Oct 2025 23:45:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It may be possible to use &lt;tt&gt;LUSTRE_OBD_UINT_PARAM_ATTR(client_limit)&lt;/tt&gt; to declare this parameter and store it in &lt;tt&gt;obd_device&lt;/tt&gt;, which is probably the easiest way to move forward.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="475234" author="adilger" created="Thu, 16 Oct 2025 23:08:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;client_limit&lt;/tt&gt; should be a normal tunable parameter, so it should already be possible to save the parameter persistently for all of the targets with e.g. &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lctl set_param -P mdt.&amp;#42;.client_limit=NNNN obdfilter.&amp;#42;.client_limit=NNNN&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;.  The &lt;tt&gt;client_limit&lt;/tt&gt; parameter can be created for the target devices like &lt;tt&gt;lustre/mdt/mdt_lproc.c::dir_split_delta&lt;/tt&gt; or &lt;tt&gt;lustre/ofd/lproc_ofd.c::brw_size&lt;/tt&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Probably the place to put the check is in &lt;tt&gt;target_handle_connect()&lt;/tt&gt; when clients are connecting. I&apos;m not exactly sure where to store the variable to &lt;br/&gt;
be accessible in the common target code.  There &lt;em&gt;used&lt;/em&gt; to be a &quot;target&quot; union in &lt;tt&gt;struct obd_device.u&lt;/tt&gt; for common target variables, but it only has client-side data there now. I&apos;m not sure what happened to it (maybe moved into &lt;tt&gt;lu_device&lt;/tt&gt; somewhere?.  Possibly &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tappro&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tappro&quot;&gt;tappro&lt;/a&gt; could comment?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
